Name: SATELLITE OFFSET INDICATOR
Explanation: THE NUMBER TO BE SET/INDICATED ON THE OFFSET SWITCH OF A SATELLITE DATA LINK TERMINAL EQUIPMENT.

Name: TRACK QUALITY LOST TRACK SUBTRACTION PARAMETER
LINK 11 NET SPEED SETTING
Explanation: THE LINK 11 NET SPEED SETTING APPLIED TO DATA LINK TERMINAL EQUIPMENT.

Name: SYSTEM SETTINGS
Explanation: THE CORRELATION/DECORRELATION SYSTEM SETTINGS ARE AUTO DEFAULT, AUTO SET OR MANUAL.

Name: WINDOW SIZE MULTIPLIER
Explanation: THE CORRELATION WINDOW SIZE MULTIPLIER TO STRETCH OR REDUCE THE WINDOW SIZE.

Name: MINIMUM WINDOW SIZE IN DATA MILES
Explanation: THE NUMBER ADDED TO THE BASIC WINDOW CALCULATED FROM TRACK QUALITIES, TO ENSURE THAT WINDOWS ARE NOT SO SMALL AS TO PREVENT VALID CORRELATIONS.

Name: MINIMUM TRACK QUALITY
Explanation: THE NUMBER TO PREVENT CORRELATION WINDOWS FROM BEING UNREALISTICALLY LARGE.

Name: MAXIMUM TRACK QUALITY
Explanation: THE NUMBER TO PREVENT CORRELATION WINDOWS FROM BEING UNREALISTICALLY SMALL BECAUSE VERY HIGH TQS ARE USED.

Name: RESTRICTED TRACK QUALITY
Explanation: A LOWER NUMBER IF IT APPEARS THAT TOO MANY DUALS INVOLVING LOW TRACK QUALITY (TQ) TRACKS ARE OCCURRING.

Name: COURSE DIFFERENTIAL IN DEGREES
Explanation: THE DEGREES OF MAXIMUM DIFFERENCE BETWEEN THE REPORTED COURSE OF THE REMOTE TRACK AND THE CALCULATED

Name: SPEED DIFFERENTIAL
Explanation: THE MAXIMUM PERCENTAGE BY WHICH THE SPEED OF THE FASTER TRACK MAY DIFFER FROM THE SPEED OF THE SLOWER TRACK.

Name: ALTITUDE DIFFERENTIAL IN HUNDREDS OF FEET
Explanation: THE MAXIMUM ALTITUDE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN TWO AIR TRACKS.

Name: MINIMUM GEODETIC POSITION QUALITY
Explanation: THE NUMBER USED FOR MINIMUM GEODETIC POSITION QUALITY.

Name: MAXIMUM GEODETIC POSITION QUALITY
Explanation: THE NUMBER USED FOR MAXIMUM GEODETIC POSITION QUALITY.

Name: DECORRELATION WINDOW MULTIPLIER
Explanation: THE DISTANCE BETWEEN THE COMMON AND REMOTE TRACK IS TO EXCEED THE APPLICABLE CORRELATION WINDOW FOR THE TWO TRACKS IN ORDER TO BE DECORRELATED.

Name: CONSECUTIVE DECORRELATIONS
Explanation: THE NUMBER OF CONSECUTIVE REMOTE TRACK REPORTS THAT MUST MEET THE DECORRELATION CRITERIA BEFORE THE DECORRELATION IS EXECUTED.

Name: SATELLITE EXTENDED TIME OUT FRAMES
Explanation: THE EXTENDED TIME OUT FRAMES FOR SATELLITE LINK 11 OPERATIONS.
